comment.body:
@Grihasss As @rockokw said you can export the sfm_data.bin file to JSON and you will see here some information for each 3D points (observations).
Observations indicate which view Id see the points and the 2D location and the feature id.
So you can load the corresponding view in Python and see if the point (x,y) is green.

If you already have the position of the ball in the images, you could also triangulate the position given the SfM camera poses.

@Grihasss Let us know if our comments help, else please elaborate exactly what you want to do.
